70.1	Danny_Hillis	W. Daniel Hillis	William Daniel "Danny" Hillis (born September 25, 1956, in Baltimore, Maryland) is an American inventor, entrepreneur, and author. He co-founded Thinking Machines Corporation, a company that developed the Connection Machine, a parallel supercomputer designed by Hillis at MIT. He is also co-founder of the Long Now Foundation, Applied Minds, Metaweb, and author of The Pattern on the Stone: The Simple Ideas That Make Computers Work.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Danny_Hillis2.jpg/200px-Danny_Hillis2.jpg
